WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-PT

00:00:06.097 --> 00:00:08.897
Questioner: What is... what is,
really, the purpose of life?

00:00:08.922 --> 00:00:11.666
Could you offer some insight into this?

00:00:11.975 --> 00:00:13.432
Thanks.

00:00:19.020 --> 00:00:21.929
Sadhguru: Isn't it fantastic that
if there is no purpose,

00:00:21.954 --> 00:00:24.427
you have nothing to accomplish,
you can simply live?

00:00:26.403 --> 00:00:27.419
Huh?

00:00:27.506 --> 00:00:29.706
No, but you want a purpose,

00:00:30.104 --> 00:00:34.147
and not just any purpose,
you want a purpose given by God.

00:00:34.350 --> 00:00:36.000
This is very dangerous.

00:00:36.249 --> 00:00:38.762
People who believe they have a

00:00:38.787 --> 00:00:41.643
God-given purpose are doing
the cruelest things on the planet.

00:00:42.765 --> 00:00:43.945
Yes or no?

00:00:45.046 --> 00:00:47.076
They are doing the most horrible things,

00:00:47.101 --> 00:00:49.913
and they have always done
the most horrible things,

00:00:50.315 --> 00:00:53.385
because when you have
a God-given purpose,

00:00:53.410 --> 00:00:58.335
life here becomes less
important than your purpose.

00:01:00.058 --> 00:01:02.375
No, life is important.

00:01:02.975 --> 00:01:05.913
Life is important —
when I say "life,"

00:01:06.418 --> 00:01:09.417
I'm not talking about
your family, your job, what

00:01:09.441 --> 00:01:12.340
you do, what
you don't do, your parties, I

00:01:12.419 --> 00:01:14.389
'm not talking about that as life.

00:01:14.414 --> 00:01:16.200
This is life, isn't it?

00:01:17.277 --> 00:01:20.039
Is life inside
you or all around you?

00:01:23.324 --> 00:01:25.208
The environment of life—

00:01:25.514 --> 00:01:28.803
you're confusing the
environment of life with life itself.

00:01:29.303 --> 00:01:34.678
Your home, your family,
your workplace, your party—

00:01:34.703 --> 00:01:36.317
all of these are the environments of life.

00:01:36.342 --> 00:01:38.152
This isn't life, is it?

00:01:38.769 --> 00:01:39.885
Yes or no?

00:01:40.582 --> 00:01:43.514
You are confusing the
environment with reality.

00:01:43.539 --> 00:01:44.562
No.

00:01:44.829 --> 00:01:46.798
Life is important

00:01:47.824 --> 00:01:49.444
because it's the only thing you know;

00:01:49.469 --> 00:01:50.757
you don't know anything else.  Do

00:01:50.782 --> 00:01:52.684
you know anything else?

00:01:53.427 --> 00:01:55.788
The rest is all imagination, isn't it?

00:01:55.813 --> 00:02:00.625
The only thing is that this one is pulsing,
alive, and that's all there is to it.

00:02:01.224 --> 00:02:02.760
So, is this important?

00:02:02.785 --> 00:02:05.403
It is extremely important.

00:02:07.106 --> 00:02:08.786
Not you as a person,

00:02:09.353 --> 00:02:10.902
that's not important,

00:02:10.927 --> 00:02:14.358
but you as a part
of life is very important,

00:02:15.469 --> 00:02:17.558
because that's the foundation of everything.

00:02:17.583 --> 00:02:19.965
When I say that this is the basis of everything,

00:02:19.990 --> 00:02:23.938
the universe exists for you only
because you exist, right?

00:02:24.394 --> 00:02:25.466
Yes or no?

00:02:26.262 --> 00:02:28.352
The world only exists for
you because you exist;

00:02:28.377 --> 00:02:31.346
otherwise, it wouldn't
exist in your experience.

00:02:31.371 --> 00:02:34.737
Therefore, in every sense,
this is important.

00:02:35.086 --> 00:02:37.777
So, what is the purpose of this?

00:02:42.453 --> 00:02:45.288
Look, if you had a
purpose and you fulfilled it,

00:02:45.313 --> 00:02:46.920
what would you do after that?

00:02:50.019 --> 00:02:51.876
After that, what would you do?

00:02:52.736 --> 00:02:54.619
You'd get bored, wouldn't you?  The thing is,

00:02:56.026 --> 00:03:01.885
life is so complex,
so phenomenally complex,

00:03:02.161 --> 00:03:07.429
that if you spent 10,000 years
observing it carefully,

00:03:07.454 --> 00:03:10.443
you still wouldn't
fully understand it.  Even

00:03:12.106 --> 00:03:16.846
if you spent a million years
observing it with absolute focus,

00:03:16.871 --> 00:03:20.012
you still wouldn't
know it completely.  That's just how

00:03:20.476 --> 00:03:22.010
things are.

00:03:23.816 --> 00:03:26.078
Is there a meaning to this?

00:03:26.292 --> 00:03:30.424
The greatest thing in life is
that it has no meaning.

00:03:31.492 --> 00:03:35.890
The greatest aspect of life
is that it has no meaning,

00:03:35.915 --> 00:03:38.615
and there is no need for
it to have any meaning.

00:03:39.257 --> 00:03:43.577
It is the smallness of the individual's mind
that will seek meaning,

00:03:43.602 --> 00:03:46.674
because, psychologically, you will feel

00:03:48.435 --> 00:03:51.497
somewhat disconnected from life

00:03:51.522 --> 00:03:54.092
if you do not have a
purpose and a meaning.

00:03:54.497 --> 00:03:58.723
People are constantly
trying to create these false purposes.

00:04:01.064 --> 00:04:04.291
Now, they were doing very well and were happy.

00:04:04.376 --> 00:04:05.851
Suddenly, they got married.

00:04:05.876 --> 00:04:09.616
Now the focus is on the other person.

00:04:10.526 --> 00:04:11.935
Then they have children.

00:04:11.960 --> 00:04:13.931
Now they've become unhappy together.

00:04:13.956 --> 00:04:15.458
"Now, the whole reason

00:04:15.483 --> 00:04:17.730
I'm going through this unhappiness
is because of the children."

00:04:18.143 --> 00:04:20.111
And so it goes.

00:04:21.692 --> 00:04:23.708
These are things that you are causing

00:04:23.733 --> 00:04:26.705
and maintaining as life purposes.  Is

00:04:27.533 --> 00:04:30.488
there a purpose given by God?

00:04:30.924 --> 00:04:33.618
What if God doesn't know you exist?

00:04:34.795 --> 00:04:37.403
No, I'm just asking, by chance.

00:04:41.692 --> 00:04:46.107
I'm saying that in this enormous cosmos,

00:04:46.514 --> 00:04:49.503
of which God should be the Creator

00:04:49.528 --> 00:04:53.487
and manager of these hundred billion galaxies,

00:04:53.512 --> 00:04:56.230
and within them is this
small planet and you...

00:04:56.255 --> 00:05:00.091
Suppose He doesn't know
you exist, what would happen?

00:05:00.900 --> 00:05:02.520
Is it possible or not?

00:05:02.893 --> 00:05:05.530
Excuse me, I'm
saying so many sacrilegious things,

00:05:05.571 --> 00:05:07.671
but is it possible or not?

00:05:07.995 --> 00:05:10.569
What if he doesn't even know you exist?

00:05:13.821 --> 00:05:16.435
What if he doesn't have a plan for you?

00:05:19.373 --> 00:05:22.939
Assume he doesn't have a plan,
an individual plan for you,

00:05:24.673 --> 00:05:27.014
don't look for such things.

00:05:27.619 --> 00:05:31.314
The point is that
creation is structured in such a way

00:05:31.339 --> 00:05:34.540
that Creation and the Creator
cannot be separated.

00:05:35.207 --> 00:05:37.048
Here, you are a part of creation.

00:05:37.073 --> 00:05:40.887
At the same time, the source of
creation is pulsing within you.

00:05:41.794 --> 00:05:45.275
If you pay a little
attention to this process of life,

00:05:45.300 --> 00:05:47.203
you won't need any purpose.

00:05:47.228 --> 00:05:50.377
He'll keep you hooked for a
million years, if you want.

00:05:50.484 --> 00:05:52.193
There's so much going on, and by

00:05:52.672 --> 00:05:54.116
"so much" I mean

00:05:54.140 --> 00:05:57.363
so many unbelievable things
happening right here.

00:05:57.388 --> 00:05:59.622
If you pay enough attention,

00:06:00.257 --> 00:06:04.230
a million years of existence
will keep you busy, or more.

00:06:04.927 --> 00:06:07.795
At this moment, the need
for a purpose has arisen

00:06:07.820 --> 00:06:11.007
because you are stuck
in the psychological structure,

00:06:11.032 --> 00:06:13.112
not in your life process.

00:06:13.458 --> 00:06:15.210
Psychologically,

00:06:15.235 --> 00:06:17.900
her psychological structure

00:06:17.925 --> 00:06:20.926
functions based on the
limited data she has accumulated.  That's what

00:06:20.951 --> 00:06:25.021
she's
spinning around in, and right now,

00:06:25.151 --> 00:06:28.907
her thoughts and emotions have become
far more important than her life.

00:06:28.932 --> 00:06:30.042
Isn't that right?

00:06:30.782 --> 00:06:31.978
Isn't that right?

00:06:32.464 --> 00:06:37.146
So, because of that, you search for
a purpose as an escape from the trap

00:06:37.577 --> 00:06:39.756
you've set for yourself.

00:06:41.213 --> 00:06:43.643
It's a trap you set.

00:06:43.927 --> 00:06:46.038
You can easily get out of it.

00:06:46.543 --> 00:06:50.482
If the trap was set for
you by someone else, it will be difficult to get out

00:06:50.507 --> 00:06:53.964
because they will set a trap in
such a way that you won't be able to escape, right?

00:06:56.546 --> 00:06:58.726
I'm talking about
life, not marriage; that's what I

00:06:58.726 --> 00:07:00.823
'm talking about.  And

00:07:04.124 --> 00:07:05.647
that.

00:07:06.759 --> 00:07:09.495
So, this is a
trap you set yourself.

00:07:09.716 --> 00:07:11.750
It's easy to get out of it,

00:07:11.786 --> 00:07:13.696
but that's the problem.

00:07:13.848 --> 00:07:16.230
The reason it's so difficult is because,

00:07:16.333 --> 00:07:19.169
now, you're
identified with the trap,

00:07:19.194 --> 00:07:20.593
you like it.

00:07:21.307 --> 00:07:25.591
You like her because she
gives you a certain sense of

00:07:27.067 --> 00:07:33.216
security, stability,
protection, and individual identity.

00:07:33.339 --> 00:07:35.838
If you build a cocoon around yourself,

00:07:36.491 --> 00:07:39.857
it gives you security,
but it also imprisons you.

00:07:40.957 --> 00:07:46.437
Walls of self-preservation
are also walls of self-imprisonment.

00:07:48.495 --> 00:07:50.856
When they protect you,
you like them.

00:07:50.942 --> 00:07:53.651
When they restrict you,
you don't like them.  That's why

00:07:55.924 --> 00:07:58.082
we have doors.

00:07:58.107 --> 00:08:01.804
We like walls
because they protect us,

00:08:01.903 --> 00:08:05.789
but we have doors so we can
open them and go out whenever we want.

00:08:05.814 --> 00:08:10.107
No matter how good it is, we
still want to go out, don't we?

00:08:11.876 --> 00:08:15.061
So, that's how it is with every
trap you set.

00:08:15.086 --> 00:08:18.352
No matter how good it is,
you still want to go out.

00:08:18.900 --> 00:08:22.163
Therefore, the psychological wall
that you have built,

00:08:22.188 --> 00:08:24.841
which gives you some sense of identity,

00:08:24.866 --> 00:08:27.629
which gives you some sense of being a person,

00:08:27.654 --> 00:08:31.851
an individual,
and which gives you security,

00:08:32.607 --> 00:08:35.059
you begin to experience it
as a trap;

00:08:35.084 --> 00:08:37.150
At some point you want to knock him down.

00:08:37.777 --> 00:08:43.653
Therefore, one way to avoid breaking it
is to find a purpose for it.

00:08:43.678 --> 00:08:46.468
Those who find
purpose in their lives

00:08:46.493 --> 00:08:48.287
become so convinced.

00:08:48.541 --> 00:08:50.973
They will live forever trapped
within their own framework,

00:08:50.998 --> 00:08:53.793
believing they are doing
the most fantastic thing.

00:08:54.016 --> 00:08:56.614
The first thing
you need is balance.

00:08:56.736 --> 00:09:00.768
If you have balance,
then you can climb.

00:09:01.057 --> 00:09:04.732
If you don't have balance, you
'd better stay on the ground, wouldn't you?  It

00:09:06.221 --> 00:09:10.477
is not safe for someone who
is not balanced to climb high.

00:09:10.683 --> 00:09:12.718
You'd better stay close to the ground.

00:09:12.743 --> 00:09:14.172
You shouldn't climb.

00:09:14.723 --> 00:09:18.159
Therefore, the first thing
is to establish a balance,

00:09:18.184 --> 00:09:20.927
then dismantle your
psychological structure, and

00:09:21.683 --> 00:09:23.420
then it will be a wonderful thing.

00:09:23.745 --> 00:09:26.899
If you dismantle your
unbalanced psychological structure—

00:09:26.924 --> 00:09:29.014
which many people do nowadays;

00:09:29.437 --> 00:09:33.336
Look, why would someone want to
drink alcohol or use drugs?

00:09:33.531 --> 00:09:35.839
Because it breaks down
your psychological structure

00:09:35.863 --> 00:09:38.221
and makes you feel free for a moment;

00:09:38.788 --> 00:09:41.320
But without the necessary balance,

00:09:42.434 --> 00:09:46.985
you haven't worked towards balance,
but you have achieved freedom.

00:09:47.322 --> 00:09:51.935
Freedom without balance
is destruction, isn't it?

00:09:53.470 --> 00:09:56.384
Therefore, the first thing
is to work towards balance,

00:09:56.409 --> 00:09:58.577
a tremendous sense of equilibrium,

00:09:58.602 --> 00:10:02.341
in which even if you
dismantle your psychological structure,

00:10:02.366 --> 00:10:04.274
you can simply live here.

00:10:04.877 --> 00:10:09.586
Dismantling your
psychological structure is an important process

00:10:09.611 --> 00:10:11.400
because it's your trap,

00:10:11.915 --> 00:10:14.776
your security, your
stability, and

00:10:14.801 --> 00:10:17.063
at the same time it's your trap,

00:10:19.207 --> 00:10:23.118
because the walls have been erected,
you feel safe,

00:10:23.143 --> 00:10:24.883
but they are also your trap.

00:10:25.296 --> 00:10:28.370
If you dismantle your trap,

00:10:29.309 --> 00:10:32.390
you'll dismantle your
security as well, won't you?

00:10:32.692 --> 00:10:35.219
You also dismantle
your sense of purpose.

00:10:35.244 --> 00:10:38.088
You also dismantle everything
that is important to you.

00:10:39.798 --> 00:10:41.622
Therefore, to achieve this,
you will need balance.

00:10:41.647 --> 00:10:45.222
Without balance, if you fall apart,
you'll go crazy.

00:10:46.485 --> 00:10:48.819
But don't look for a purpose,

00:10:48.819 --> 00:10:51.022
because if you look for a purpose,

00:10:51.927 --> 00:10:53.713
you're looking for madness.

00:10:53.738 --> 00:10:57.181
If you find one,
you're definitely crazy.

00:10:58.935 --> 00:10:59.958
Yes.

00:11:01.135 --> 00:11:03.476
If you think you've found
a purpose in life,

00:11:03.501 --> 00:11:06.513
you've definitely gone mad,

00:11:08.312 --> 00:11:11.248
because only
mad people have a purpose,

00:11:12.099 --> 00:11:17.026
or people who have a purpose
are mad in many ways.

00:11:17.262 --> 00:11:19.568
These are things you create in your mind

00:11:19.593 --> 00:11:21.585
and believe to be
true, right?  Right

00:11:21.680 --> 00:11:25.917
now,
"fighting for my country is my purpose," and

00:11:26.499 --> 00:11:28.974
 
if necessary, I will fight,

00:11:28.998 --> 00:11:32.175
knowing full well that it's
a damn unnecessary fight.

00:11:33.933 --> 00:11:34.950
Yes.

00:11:34.975 --> 00:11:37.767
That way, you'll only fight
to the extent necessary.

00:11:37.792 --> 00:11:39.580
If you think that's your purpose,

00:11:39.605 --> 00:11:41.445
you'll want to destroy the whole world

00:11:41.470 --> 00:11:43.679
because of the nonsense
you believe, won't you?

00:11:45.317 --> 00:11:47.692
If something is necessary,
we will do it,

00:11:48.917 --> 00:11:50.780
with absolute commitment.  There

00:11:50.805 --> 00:11:52.021
is no other purpose.

00:11:52.046 --> 00:11:55.294
The purpose of life is to
live, and to live fully.

00:11:55.741 --> 00:11:58.870
Living life to the fullest doesn't mean
partying every night.  To

00:12:02.194 --> 00:12:03.986
live life fully means

00:12:03.986 --> 00:12:07.498
that, before you die,
every aspect of life has been explored,

00:12:07.498 --> 00:12:09.588
nothing has been left unexplored.

00:12:10.421 --> 00:12:11.536
Yes?

00:12:11.851 --> 00:12:16.124
Before you die,
even if you don't explore the cosmos,

00:12:16.157 --> 00:12:19.915
at least you should experience this part of life
in its entirety.

00:12:19.940 --> 00:12:22.634
This is something you have to
do for yourself, isn't it?

00:12:22.902 --> 00:12:27.541
That's what it means to live fully,
to experience all of this,

00:12:27.566 --> 00:12:29.927
all the dimensions of what this is.

00:12:29.952 --> 00:12:32.303
You left nothing untouched.

00:12:33.726 --> 00:12:35.083
Just do that.  It

00:12:35.108 --> 00:12:36.573
will take a long time.

00:12:36.598 --> 00:12:38.913
It's a good enough purpose for you.

